# [PROJECT_NAME] — Claude Code Configuration

> **Version:** agentic-dev-framework v[VERSION]  
> **Setup:** Copy this file to `CLAUDE.md` in your project root. Replace `[PROJECT_NAME]` and `[VERSION]`. Run `BOOTSTRAP.prompt.md` to resolve all `{{TOKEN}}` placeholders.

This file configures Claude Code for use with the agentic-dev-framework. It provides Claude with the same quality constraints, agent routing, and session context defined in `.github/copilot-instructions.md` — because Claude.md has independent context from `.github/` in some Claude Code configurations.

---

## Framework

This project uses agentic-dev-framework v[VERSION]. Full agent definitions, skills, and path-scoped instructions live in `.github/`. This file encodes the subset Claude needs to operate correctly without reading every `.github/` file on every request.

**Specification:** `docs/FRAMEWORK-SPEC.md` defines the four core contracts this adapter implements.

---

## Session Start Protocol (Always — Before Every Response)

Before responding to any request, read these files:

1. `docs/project-intelligence.md` — Anti-patterns and locked architectural decisions apply to all work in this session. Do not repeat known anti-patterns.
2. `docs/open-handoffs.md` — Check for OPEN handoffs. Do not proceed with work that an OPEN handoff is blocking.
3. `.github/copilot-instructions.md` — Global constraints, agent scope boundaries, and repository standards. The Constraints (Non-Negotiable) section is duplicated below for immediate access.

If any of these files is missing or unreadable, note the gap but continue — do not fail the session start.

