## Agent Routing

When the user references an agent by name or invocation shorthand, apply the corresponding agent definition from `.github/agents/`:

| User Says | Agent File | Primary Scope |
|-----------|-----------|---------------|
| `@pm` or "product manager" | `.github/agents/thoughtful-product-manager.agent.md` | Feature fit, roadmap, acceptance criteria |
| `@architect` | `.github/agents/system-architect.agent.md` | System structure, API design, data model |
| `@engineer` | `.github/agents/engineer.agent.md` | Implementation, verification, delivery |
| `@qa` | `.github/agents/veteran-qa.agent.md` | Test plans, regression, release readiness |
| `@designer` | `.github/agents/bold-ux-designer.agent.md` | Visual hierarchy, UX, result discoverability |
| `@technical-writer` | `.github/agents/technical-writer.agent.md` | Documentation governance, consolidation |
| `@review-council` | `.github/agents/review-council.agent.md` | 7-perspective code and architecture review |
| `@accessibility` | `.github/agents/accessibility.agent.md` | WCAG 2.1 AA, keyboard nav, screen reader |
| `@devops-infrastructure` | `.github/agents/devops-infrastructure.agent.md` | Containers, CI/CD, deployment health |
| `@performance` | `.github/agents/performance.agent.md` | Bundle size, query efficiency, response times |
| `@innovator` | `.github/agents/innovator.agent.md` | Problem reframing, solution scouting |
| `@researcher` | `.github/agents/researcher.agent.md` | Evidence gathering, multi-perspective research |

When an agent is invoked, read its `.agent.md` file fully before responding. The agent's constraints, decision pattern, and output format are binding for that session.

