## Institutional Memory

These two files encode project-specific knowledge accumulated over the project's lifetime. They are the primary reason the Session Start Protocol requires reading them first.

**`docs/project-intelligence.md`** — Anti-patterns discovered, locked architectural decisions, coverage hot spots, and acknowledged technical debt. When you discover a new anti-pattern or architectural decision in a session, add it to this file before the session closes.

**`docs/open-handoffs.md`** — Cross-agent escalations using SBAR format (Situation, Background, Assessment, Decision Needed). Check for OPEN handoffs at session start. Do not proceed with implementation while an OPEN handoff blocks your area of work. Update status to `RESOLVED` when an escalation is addressed.

